Vice President Mike Pence delivered a speech at the 2017 Summit for the National Association of Manufacturers, praising the organization for advocating for American manufacturers and highlighting their importance to the economy. He emphasized the Trump administration's commitment to supporting manufacturers and creating a favorable business environment through initiatives such as deregulation, energy reform, and workforce development. Pence also promised that the administration would repeal and replace Obamacare, pass tax cuts, and invest in infrastructure. He concluded by affirming the administration's dedication to strengthening American manufacturing and ensuring a prosperous and secure future for the country.